<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idf6bfa66e-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5" identifier="/us/usc/t46/s51305"><num value="51305">§ 51305.</num><heading> Prohibited basis for appointment</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Preference may not be given to an individual for appointment as a cadet at the United States Merchant Marine Academy because one or more members of the individual’s immediate family are alumni of the Academy.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idf6bfa66f-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5">(<ref href="/us/pl/109/304/s8/b">Pub. L. 109–304, § 8(b)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-06">Oct. 6, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1572">120 Stat. 1572</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
